Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a theory of concurrency for ensuring liveness properties of distributed systems without making fairness assumptions. This involves the study of process algebra, temporal logic, and semantic models, as well as treatments of real-time. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the need for new induction principles, axiomatic bases, and congruence formats, which are topics covered in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the application of this theory to routing protocols for wireless networks, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
